      "content": "yeah, if we look at the descent phase for Apollo 11, there's a massive gap in the signal strength right as they were supposedly settling into the landing site. it's like the comms just flatlined for a few minutes before coming back online. why would a perfectly functioning lander just lose signal for a bit during the most critical part of the mission? it makes me think they were actually transmitting something directly from the structure itself and had to cut the feed to hide it. what kind of patterns would we expect to see in the telemetry if they were trying to mask a massive, non-terrestrial signal?",
